rtak Kostroma]]   | caps5  = 35 | goals5  = 5 \n| years6  = 2012\u20132015 | clubs6  = [[FC Arsenal Tula]]       | caps6  = 75 | goals6  = 5\n| years7  = 2015\u20132016 | clubs7  = [[FC Tom Tomsk]]          | caps7  = 23 | goals7  = 1\n| years8  = 2017      | clubs8  = [[FC Anzhi Makhachkala]]  | caps8  =  0 | goals8  = 0\n| years9  = 2017\u20132018 | clubs9  = [[FC Shinnik Yaroslavl]]  | caps9  = 23 | goals9  = 0\n| years10 = 2018\u2013     | clubs10 = [[FC Torpedo Moscow]]     | caps10 = 23 | goals10 = 0\n| pcupdate = 2 June 2019\n| ntupdate =\n}}\n\n'''Andrei Ivanovich Lyakh''' ({{lang-ru|\u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0439 \u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u041b\u044f\u0445}}; born 24 September 1990) is a [[Russia]]n professional [[Association football|football]] player. He plays for [[FC Torpedo Moscow]].\n\n==Club career==\nHe made his [[Russian Premier League]] debut for [[FC Arsenal Tula]] on 2 August 2014 in a game against [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg]].\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is a son of [[Ivan Lyakh]].\n\n==External links==\n* [http://news.sportbox.ru/Vidy_sporta/Futbol/stats/man_1240738243 Player page by sportbox.ru]\n* {{RPL player|Lyah-Andrey}}\n\n{{FC Torpedo Moscow squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lyakh, Andrei}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Rostov-on-Don]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Russian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:FC Zhemchuzhina Sochi players]]\n[[Category:Russian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Lithuania]]\n[[Category:FC Arsenal Tula players]]\n[[Category:Russian Premier League players]]\n[[Category:FC Tom Tomsk players]]\n[[Category:FC Shinnik Yaroslavl players]]\n[[Category:FC Rostov players]]\n[[Category:FC Torpedo Moscow players]]\n[[Category:FC Anzhi Makhachkala players]]\n[[Category:FC Khimik Dzerzhinsk players]]\n[[Category:People from Rostov-on-Don]]\n[[Category:FC Spartak Kostroma players]]\n\n\n{{Russia-footy-